   <property name="title">
    <string>Grades 0-2</string>
   </property>
   <layout class="QVBoxLayout" name="verticalLayout_4">
    <item>
     <widget class="QLabel" name="grades02_lbl">
      <property name="text">
       <string>Grades range from 0 to 5.

Grades 0 and 1 are used if you don't know the answer yet, or if you have forgotten this card. A card with grade 1 is starting to get more familiar than one with grade 0, and will be repeated less often.

I will keep on asking you these questions until you give them a grade 2 or higher. This basically means that you think you'll be able to remember the card for at least one or two days. It signals the transition between short and long term memory.

I will schedule this card at some future date, when I think you'll still be able to remember it with some effort, without having forgotten it completely. This is the most efficient for the learning process.</string>
